<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ten Civilians Injured in Indian firing: APP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 civilians including
seven women were injured in "unprovoked and indiscriminate" mortar
firing by the Indian army across the Line of Control (LoC) on
Sunday evening, Pakistan's state media reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP), the Indian
army began heavy shelling at about 17:30 p.m. local time (1230 GMT)
on the border village of Shamali Barmoch in Tatta Pani sector in
the Pakistan-administered Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The shelling resulted in injuring of 10 members of three
families of the village, six of them critically, APP quoted local
police sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
All the injured were admitted in a local hospital, said the
report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
