<HEADLINE> Mongolian Parties Prepared to Compete in Parliament Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian Political parties
and coalitions have started to register at the General Electoral
Committee to be qualified to compete in the third election of the
State Great Khural (Mongolian Parliament) scheduled for July 2,
2000.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last week, the Mongolian Democratic New Socialist
Party (MDNSP) was handed the first certificate to compete in the
upcoming parliament election.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian Republican Party (MRP) and the Mongolian
Democratic Party (MDP) were listed today in names of parties that
would run for the July election.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the Mongolian Social Democratic Party (MSDP)
had separated from its coalition with the Mongolian National
Democratic Party (MNDP) and will run for the upcoming parliament
election independently.
</P>
<P>
According to the Parliament Election Law, political parties and
coalitions have to send programs and applications for
participating in the election to the General Electoral Committee
65 days before the election.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 24 political parties were officially registered in
Mongolia, of which only 3 parties, the Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party (MPRP), the MSDP and the MNDP are ruling
parties.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest polling results organized by Sant Maral
Foundation, 51.7 percent of the voters will cast their ballots to
support the MPRP. The party is far ahead of the second biggest
party, party of Civic Courage, which gets support of the 9 percent
of the voters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
