<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Safety of Tibetans Ensured in Landslide Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Tibet
Autonomous Region adopted effective measures to protect the safety
of people in Yigong Township in Bomi County, Nyingchi Prefecture,
where a landslide occurred earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Large landslides followed by mud and rock flows struck the
township on April 9, destroying seven kilometers of highways and
stranding more than 4,000 residents.
</P>
<P>
Now, 1,158 residents have been removed to safer areas and the
rest are preparing to leave the landslide area.
</P>
<P>
Also, the State Flood Control Headquarters sent a group of 10
experts to Tibet to help the local government make rescue plans.
</P>
<P>
In the past few days, various sectors have donated money, and
relief materials have been transported to the landslide area.
</P>
<P>
The Education Bureau of Nyingchi Prefecture was responsible
for seeing that 140 primary school students were sent to nearby
counties to resume their classes.
</P>
<P>
No outbreaks of epidemic diseases or casualties have been
reported so far in the wake of this disaster.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
