<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Sino-S. African Friendship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRETORIA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here Tuesday evening that the Pretoria Declaration on
the Partnership between China and South Africa signed earlier on
the day marked a new stage of the development of the bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that if our two peoples unite as one and cooperate
extensively, we will be able to make new contribution to the
progress and development of mankind," said Jiang at a banquet
hosted by South African President Thabo Mbeki in Jiang's honor.
</P>
<P>
Both being important developing countries in Asia and Africa,
China and South Africa share the same goals in safeguarding the
rights and interests of developing countries and promoting the
establishment of a peaceful, stable, just and equitable new
international political and economic order, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said to strengthen the cooperation between the
two countries serves the fundamental interests of the two peoples
and the peace and development of the world.
</P>
<P>
The past several years have witnessed remarkable progress the
new South Africa, which was founded in 1994, has made in promoting
national reconciliation, developing national economy and improving
people's life, Jiang said, adding that South Africa is playing an
increasingly important role in regional and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
"We sincerely hope that under the leadership of President
Mbeki, the people of South Africa will score fresh achievements
continuously in the lofty cause of building up their country," he
said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang is on a state visit to South Africa at the
invitation of Mbeki. The five-nation tour has brought him to
Israel, Palestine, Turkey and Greece. Jiang also met with Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak in the Alexandria city of Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
