<HEADLINE> 38 Angolans Killed in Landmine Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-eight people have been
killed by an anti-tank mine in the northern Uige province of
Angola when it was triggered by vehicles running on the
Puri-Negage road, official news agency Angop reported here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to mayor of the Negage District Garcia Fanana, 33 of
the victims were killed immediately on the spot near Quimussunda
and Quisseque Bento village, while the other five died Monday dawn
at the hospital.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred when the victims were on their way back
to the city of Uige, capital of the Uige Province, after a visit
to the "November 11" village in Sanza Pombo District where they
usually exchange some products like salt, fish and clothes, Fanana
said.
</P>
<P>
This is the second tragedy caused by landmines on the same road
within a month. The first killed eight people.
</P>
<P>
During the 26-year civil conflict, more than 11 million mines
have been laid in the country with a population of 10 million,
killing innumerable civilians and leaving 150,000 handicapped,
local analysts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
