<DOCNO> XIE20000425.0041 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets PM of Gauteng Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRETORIA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here on Tuesday that the Gauteng Province of South Africa
should enhance its contacts and exchanges with Beijing, which has
forged friendly ties with the province.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks when meeting with Mbhazima Shilowa,
Prime Minister of the Gauteng Province.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciation for the achievements the
province has made in recent years, and hoped that the province
will make new contributions to the advancement of the Sino-South
African ties.
</P>
<P>
Shilowa said that his province values its ties with China and
has scored progress in economic cooperation with Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The province will continue to pursue friendly cooperation with
China in accordance with the guideline adopted during the talks
between the two heads of the states on Tuesday, he added.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang is here on his last leg of the five-nation
tour. The visit has brought him to Israel, Palestine, Turkey and
Greece. Jiang also met with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in
the Alexandria city of Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
