<HEADLINE> Silver Down, Gold Steady in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Silver prices turned weak on
the bullion market in Mumbai (Bombay) Tuesday due to a fall in the
international prices while gold prices held steady.
</P>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness) opened weak at 7,970 rupees (185.
35 U.S. dollars) per kilogram and declined sharply towards the fag-
end and closed at 7,940 rupees (184.65 dollars), showing a fresh
fall of 35 rupees (0.81 dollar) over the last close of 7,975
rupees (185.46 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) closed at 7,795 rupees (181.28
dollars) per kg. from 7,830 rupees (182.09 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, standard gold and twenty-two-carat gold held steady
at 4,450 rupees (103.49 dollars) per 10 grams and 4,115 rupees (95.
70 dollars). 
</P>
