<HEADLINE> Sensex Gains Moderately on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (Sensex)
rose moderately on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) Tuesday on
heavy purchases by Foreign Funds and Financial Institutions.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share Sensitive Index opened sharply down at 4,336.
64 and crashed to the day's low of 4,284.17. Later the sensex
bounced back with a vengeance and closed at 4,533.99 as against
Monday's close of 4,511.05, netting a moderate gain of 22.94
points.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index, however, fell by 24.56 points to 2,400.99
from the previous close of 2,425.55.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted remarkably down at
512.53 and 195.49 compared with the previous close of 519.06 and
197.98 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index softened by 23.43 points to 1,540.60 from
Monday's close of 1,564.03. 
</P>
