<HEADLINE> Chinese President Reiterates China's Stance on Taiwan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRETORIA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here Tuesday that China always adheres to the principles of
peaceful reunification and "one country, two systems" in the
settlement of the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"We said in the past, and still hold that no matter who is in
power in Taiwan, we all welcome them to come to the mainland for
talks, and we can also go to Taiwan for the negotiation," Jiang
said during his talks with South African President Thabo Mbeki.
</P>
<P>
"However, the one China principle is the prerequisite of the
dialogues and talks," he stressed. "Under this prerequisite, we
can make discussions on everything."
</P>
<P>
"We would like to exchange views on the relations across the
Taiwan Straits and peaceful reunification with all parties,
organizations and personnel in Taiwan which support the one China
principle," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived here on Monday for a four-day state visit, which
is the first by a Chinese head of state to South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Jiang will also visit Cape Town after holding talks with South
African president in Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is the last leg of Jiang's five-nation trip, which
also took him to Israel, Palestine, Turkey and Greece. 
</P>
