<HEADLINE> Swiss Police Investigate Into Bomb Attacks in Bern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Swiss police started an
investigation on Tuesday into two bomb attacks in the capital of
Bern against the defense ministry and the government's new
intelligence coordinator.
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in the explosions and the damage was minor,
said the police.
</P>
<P>
According to Swiss Radio International, a left-wing extremist
group has claimed responsibility for Tuesday's explosions.
</P>
<P>
The radio report said the group, called the "Revolutionary
Perspective", sent a letter to the police claiming that it
launched the attacks aimed at an exhibition on the Swiss army due
to open in Basel this week.
</P>
<P>
The group hit the Belgian consulate in Zurich in a paint bomb
attack in 1998, said the report.
</P>
<P>
One of the two explosive devices was planted at the house of
the government's new intelligence coordinator Jacques Pitteloud,
and the other outside a building housing offices of the defense
ministry in the city of Bern.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the defense ministry condemned the attacks,
saying that the army exhibition would go ahead as planned.
</P>
</TEXT>
