<HEADLINE> East China Schools to Aid Education in Poorer Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council today held a forum to mobilize schools in eastern China
and major cities in western China to aid their counterparts in the
poverty-stricken areas of the west.
</P>
<P>
Xu Rongkai, deputy secretary-general of the State Council, said
that this aid should include not only materials, but also cadres
and teachers.
</P>
<P>
He encouraged students and teachers to establish ties between
schools in the cities and those in the poor areas.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Education Chen Zhili said that the education sector
should realize the importance and significance of giving such aid
to the country's underdeveloped region.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education and five other ministries have
jointly issued a circular on the guiding principles for 125
schools in eastern China and major cities to select similar
schools in poor regions as partners in the assistance program.
</P>
<P>
Teenagers in eastern China are also urged to make friends with
pupils in these poorer regions for common progress in their
studies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
