<HEADLINE> Major Highway in Southwest China to be Complete Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A major modern highway linking
southwest China's Chongqing Municipality to the port city of
Zhanjiang in South China's Guangdong Province will be completed
next year, according to Vice Minister of Communications Li Juchang.
</P>
<P>
The 1,314 kilometer-long highway will run through Guizhou
Province and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, with the
Qinzhou to Baihai section in Guangxi to be finished by October 1,
this year.
</P>
<P>
Li said the construction of this highway will lay a solid
foundation for the country's drive to develop the western region
and boost the development of local economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
