<HEADLINE> Iranian Defense Minister Urges Gulf Common Security  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Minister of Defense and
Armed Forces Logistics Ali Shamkhani categorically denied the
rumors about a schemed military revolt against the government of
moderate president Mohammed Khatami.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure from Tehran to Saudi Arabia on Monday
evining, Shamkani said, in an interview with London-based Saudi
Arabic Middle East daily printed on Tuesday, that the Iranian
people have been rapidly advancing toward civil community and
democracy as in the perspective of president Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
On the security and defense co-operation between Iran and the
Gulf Co-operation Council(GCC), he said Iran believes in the need
to establish a pattern of inclusive security co-ordination in the
region by the Gulf countries, stressing that the security of the
Gulf and the region should be the common responsibilty of the Gulf
states.
</P>
<P>
He repeatedly stressed Iran's stand against foreign presence in
the Gulf region, calling on the U.S troops to abandon the Persian
Gulf.
</P>
<P>
Such presence can provide mere short-run balance while Iran
hopefully aspire for permanent and firm regional security and
stability, he explained.
</P>
<P>
The western countries, which sell such huge arms arsenal
including the chemical weapons to the regional states, added to the
tension and insecurity there, he pointed out, stressing that Iran
holds the view that co-operation and solidarity are decisive in
maintaining stability and security in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
Shamkahni, who later arrived in Riyadh, discussed in the Red Sea
resort of Jeddah on Monday evening with Saudi First Deputy Prime
Minister, Minister of Defense and Aviation Prince Sultan ibn Abd
el-Aziz the means to promote military co-operation between Iran and
Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
