The visit comes after the remarks made last week by French
Defense Minister Alain Richard that he was reconsidering the "
Syrian hegemony" over Lebanon triggered anger from Lebanon and its
major power broker Syria.
</P>
<P>
Shareh will also discuss with top French officials Israel's
planned withdrawal from south Lebanon by July, under the U.N.
Security Council Resolutions 425 and 426, diplomatic sources here
said.
</P>
<P>
The talks will also tackle the U.N. role in securing such a
withdrawal and removing the obstacles hindering the resumption of
the Israeli-Syrian talks, which have been stalled since January.
</P>
<P>
France is seeking to participate in the peace keeping mission in
south lebanon after the Israeli pullout, pursuing assurances from
the relevant parties on guaranteeing the safety of these soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet early last month endorsed Prime Minister
Ehud Barak's plans to pull Israeli soldiers out of south Lebanon by
July, with or without a peace agreement with Lebanon and Syria.
</P>
<P>
Israel has formally informed U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
of the withdrawal on April 17. 
