<HEADLINE> Over 9,000 UNITA Rebels Surrender </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Over 9,000 Angolan rebels have
surrendered themselves to the government and joined the government
troops in the past few days, the Angolan Armed Forces (FAA)
announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Some high ranking rebel officers said that to continue serving
Jonas Savimbi, leader of the National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA), was the same as having a "lost
life", according to the Angola Press.
</P>
<P>
"The life of those individuals is a lost one. There is no
future on the other side," says colonel Luis Jorge, a former rebel
officer.
</P>
<P>
The FAA considered the surrender of those former rebel fighters
 as contribution to the government strategies to wipe out UNITA
military capability in the long-term civil war. 
</P>
