<HEADLINE> COMESA, SADC Complete Vehicle Road Fees Study </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) and the Southern African Development
Community (SADC) have completed a joint study aimed at coming up
with a common road charge for heavy duty vehicles.
</P>
<P>
COMESA assistant secretary-general Sindiso Ngwenya has revealed
that the two regional groupings realized the importance of
maintaining a good road and communication network in the regions.
</P>
<P>
"With SADC, we did a joint study on road user charges aimed at
coming up with what to charge on buses and trucks so that they pay
one fee based on the damage they do to the road. The charge will
focus on the individual contribution of the wear and tear of the
road," Ngwenya was quoted by Tuesday's Zambia Daily Mail newspaper
as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The common road user charge with SADC is just one in many
projects which we are working on to develop the regions'
infrastructure," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ngwenya could not say when the common user fee would be
implemented in COMESA and SADC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
