<HEADLINE> Boys Set Fire on McDonald's After Refused French Fry Offer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Three boys aged from 14 to 15 set
fire on a playground outside a McDonald's restaurant last weekend
in retaliation for the refusal by the restaurant staff to offer
them French fries, said police on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The incident drew great attention from the public because it
came shortly after a bombing attack was staged against another
McDonald's in Brittany, western France, in which one woman
employee was killed.
</P>
<P>
The three boys admitted to police in Bayonne, southwestern
France, that they had also set a series of fire on dustbins and
post boxes this year.
</P>
<P>
The worst damage was done when they destroyed an electric
circuit system, causing a loss of some 200,000 francs (about 30,
000 U.S. dollars) in public properties.
</P>
<P>
The boys were arrested when they were setting fire on a dustbin
outside a young man's garments shop Sunday night. 
</P>
