<HEADLINE> Six Assistant Procurators-General of Macao SAR Sworn In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The overall framework of the
procuratorates of the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR)
has been completed with six assistant procurators-general
inaugurated Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"The inauguration indicates that the judicial system in the SAR
has entered a new phase under the guidance of the Macao Basic Law,
" Procurator-General Ho Chio Meng said.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law, procuratorates and courts are the
judiciary of the Macao SAR. With the existence of three-level
courts in the SAR, namely the Court of Final Appeal, Intermediate
Court and primary courts, the procurator-general, assistant
procurators-general and procurators are able to well exercise
judicial responsibilities together with corresponding judges, Ho
said.
</P>
<P>
"Acting as backbone members, the (assistant) procurators-
general will become good examples of procurators in terms of their
professional knowledge and personal integrity," the procurator-
general said. "We are fully aware of the important
responsibilities we shoulder in building a democratic, law-ruling,
fair and progressive society in Macao," he said, adding that the
main task of the procuratorates this year is to crack down on
crimes and safeguard the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the procurators will ensure that law-
enforcement is carried out in strict accordance with the law, the
procurator-general said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
