<HEADLINE> China to Become Largest Projector Market in Asia-Pacific </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China is likely to become the
largest market of computer projectors in Asia-Pacific region, a
senior official of the world's top projector producer said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Vincent Leung, Asia-Pacific marketing manager of InFocus, told
a press conference today that China has already surpassed
Australia as the second largest market of projectors in the region,
following Japan.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that the market for projectors in China will grow
to 15,000 units of low-end products and 34,000 units of high-end
products this year.
</P>
<P>
Leung said that after its merger with the second largest
projector producer in the world by the end of June, InFocus will
continue to invest heavily in China because it is one of the
fastest growing projector market in the world.
</P>
<P>
For every 100 notebook computers sold in China market, 4-5
projectors are sold. Noting that since only 10 percent of personal
computers in China are notebook, Leung said that China will soon
catch up with the international average of 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
He said that China also has a big market potential of
connecting projectors with desktop computers and networks.
</P>
<P>
InFocus introduced the world's smallest notebook projector to
the China market today.
</P>
<P>
InFocus reported revenue of 390 million US dollars for the
fiscal year ending December 31, 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
