<HEADLINE> Chinese Legislature Urges Development of Seed Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislature has urged
that the production, trade, and use of seeds be standardized to
protect the interests of those involved in the country's forestry
and farming sectors.
</P>
<P>
The Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC),
which opened its 15th meeting here today, heard a report on
revising the draft of the Seed Law by the NPC Law Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Law Committee proposed that the state support the
protection of seed resources as well as the breeding, production,
and spreading of high-quality seeds.
</P>
<P>
The committee urged stricter controls on the breeding,
experimenting, and spreading of transgenetic plant seeds, and on
importing major seeds from abroad.
</P>
<P>
Farmers should be allowed to sell the extra seeds they have
produced, the committee proposed, and also suggested stepping up
the integration of the research, production, and trade of seeds by
various sectors.
</P>
<P>
Sino-foreign seed producing joint ventures should be allowed to
be established in accordance with laws stipulated for all Sino-
foreign joint ventures, the committee said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
