<HEADLINE> Share Prices Slightly Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed slightly
firmer on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday buoyed by gains in SIA
and banking stocks.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 17.18 points to
end at 2,066.96 points in thin trading.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 202.62 million shares
worth 356.66 million Singapore dollars (209.39 million U.S.
dollars). Advancing issues edged out decliners by 180 to 125 with
224 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 15.77 million parcel by East Tech
which was transacted at 1.13 Singapore dollars per unit. It was
followed by Ho Pro which had 10.66 million shares done. AirOcean
was the next with 10.39 million shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
ShangAsia headed the ascent of the day as it gained 65 cents to
close at 8.80 Hong Kong dollars. Creative 50 and SIA picked up 60
cents each to finish at 37.40 and 17.80 Singapore dollars
respectively. SIA 200, SIA DBScw00 and SPH edged up 50 cents to
end at 7.80, 11.60 and 30.40 Singapore dollars separately.
</P>
<P>
Venture led losers of the day incurring a loss of 70 cents to
end at 17.30 Singapore dollars. CMSPort and PacCent fell by 30
cents to finish at 3.00 Hong Kong dollars and 12.90 Singapore
dollars respectively. SCS dipped by 16 cents to end at 3.34
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the rise was mainly propelled by the stock of the
Singapore Airlines (SIA) which announced Tuesday that it has
acquired 16.7 percent of Air New Zealand bringing to a total of 25
percent of its share in the airlines.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the proposed listing of two of its unit, dealers
said the counter was also ripe for bargain hunting given that it
did not enjoy much buying activity over the past weeks.
</P>
<P>
Dealers also said Tuesday's volume was relatively thin and the
market had been in quiet down-trend since last week, noting
sentiment was also dampened by the U.S. NASDAQ's overnight fall.
</P>
</TEXT>
