<HEADLINE> Dutch Eagerly to Prove Euro 2000 Favorites Label </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Joint hosts the Netherlands
fielded a full-strength team for Wednesday's warm-up match against
Scotland, seeking to prove their favorites label for this summer's
European Championships.
</P>
<P>
Dutch coach Frank Rijkaard welcome back Arsenal striker Dennis
Bergkamp and Barcelona's Boudewijn Zenden, while Vitesse Arnhem's
Pierre van Hooijdonk and Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink of Atletico
Madrid are also in the squad. Only Barca defender Ronald de Boer
is missing with a groin injury.
</P>
<P>
Scotland manager Craig Brown had to reshuffle his squad on
Sunday after Coventry City's Paul Telfer and Colin Hendry,
Newcastle United's Kevin Gallacher and Barry Ferguson of Glasgow
Rangers all pulled out with injuries.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's match will be the 13th meeting between the two
sides. Of the last 12, the Dutch have won five, the Scots four,
while three games, including the last meeting during Euro 96, have
ended in a draw.
</P>
<P>
Probable teams:
</P>
<P>
Netherlands: Edwin van der Sar; Frank de Boer, Jaap Stam,
Winston Bogarde, Michael Reiziger; Philip Cocu, Clarence Seedorf,
Edgar Davids; Mark Overmars, Patrick Kluivert, Dennis Bergkamp
</P>
<P>
Scotland: Neil Sullivan; David Weir, Matt Elliott, Christian
Dailly; Craig Burley, Paul Lambert, Ian Durrant, Jackie McNamara,
Colin Cameron; Don Hutchinson, Billy Dodds
</P>
<P>
Referee: Hartmut Strampe (Germany) 
</P>
