<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Win Opening Match in Fed Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Second-seeded China won the opening
match of the Federation Cup Asia-Oceania zone qualifying rounds
Tuesday together with Indonesia, Chinese Taipei and Kazakhstan in
Osaka, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Fourth-seeded Thailand suffered an upset to India.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the Asia-Oceania Zone Group I will advance to the
elite World Group of the Fed Cup women tennis competition in 2001.
</P>
<P>
In the five-nation Pool A round-robin competition at the Utsubo
Tennis hard court in western Japan, India beat fourth seeds
Thailand 2-1 and Kazakhstan defeated Hong Kong, China, 2-1.
</P>
<P>
In the six-nation Pool B competition, China beat South Korea 2-
1, third-seeded Chinese Taipei defeated Singapore 3-0 and
Indonesia defeated New Zealand 3-0.
</P>
<P>
The round-robin competition will last until Saturday. The
winners of Pool A and Pool B meet on Sunday to decide the champion
in the Asia-Oceania zone.
</P>
<P>
In the Group II, Uzbekistan defeated Pacific Oceania 2-1 and
Malaysia defeated Fiji 3-0 in the five-nation round-robin Pool A
competition.
</P>
<P>
In the six-nation Pool B competition, Sri Lanka defeated
Pakistan 2-1, Tajikistan defeated Syria 3-0 and the Philippines
defeated Jordan 3-0.
</P>
<P>
The winner of Group II will be replaced with the last team in
Group I. 
</P>
</TEXT>
