Li said the Chinese Communist Party and government both
treasure the bilateral friendship between the two countries, which
was initiated and fostered by Chinese leaders of the elder
generation and King Norodom Sihanouk.
</P>
<P>
To further consolidate the good-neighborliness between China
and Cambodia is not only in the fundamental interest of the two
countries, but also beneficial to peace, stability and development
of Asia and even the world at large, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Sirivudh reaffirmed the Cambodian government will, as always,
stick to the "one China" policy, adding he himself is willing to
do more to stimulate communication and cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The prince, who severs as senior advisor to King Sihanouk and
chairman of the council of the Cambodian Institute of Cooperation
and Peace, is visiting China as guest of the Chinese Association
for International Understanding. 
</P>
