<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stricter Rules to Be Issued to Reduce Air Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China will take measures to
prevent the spreading of dust and sand in some areas and help them
reduce air pollutants.
</P>
<P>
Delegates to the 15th meeting of the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee today heard a report on the
approval of the Draft Law on the Prevention of Air Pollution of
the People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
Some members of the NPC Standing Committee said that norms for
charges levied for air pollutant discharge should be worked out in
accordance with the need of the air pollution control and the
current economic development and technical level.
</P>
<P>
They also suggested that industrial production facilities which
pollute the environment should not be built in scenic spots,
nature reserves and other areas under special protection.
</P>
<P>
The pollution discharge of some enterprises in acid-rain and
sulfur dioxide-affected areas should be controlled, according to
the Environment and Resource Protection Committee of the NPC.
</P>
<P>
Motor vehicles should be modified according to state air
pollution regulations, so that all vehicles will reach the state
emission standards.
</P>
<P>
The Draft Law on the Air Pollution Prevention, which has been
discussed and revised twice by the NPC Standing Committee, will be
able to meet the need for stricter control and prevention of air
pollution in China, according to NPC members to the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
