<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) this afternoon announced
the dismissal of Cheng Kejie from the post of vice-chairman of the
NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at the ongoing 15th meeting of the NPC
Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
After reviewing the draft of an announcement from the committee
on the dismissal, the legislators voted unanimously to remove
Cheng from the post.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, Cheng, who has been accused of
abusing power and accepting huge bribes in disregard of the state
laws, was deprived of his delegacy to the NPC by the regional
people's congress of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region on April
21.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee passed the resolution to dismiss
Cheng as vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee in accordance
with the Law on Election of the National People's Congress and
Local People's Congresses of Different Levels, the announcement
says.  
