<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A violent storm that swept
eastern Nepal Monday claimed at least three lives and injured many
others,according to a report reaching here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
One couple were killed when their house collapsed, while a
woman was crushed to death when a trees fell on her, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of people were seriously injured in the storm, it said.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary estimates showed that property worth millions of
rupees (70 rupees equal one U.S. dollar) was destroyed by the
storm, which has left a trail of destruction in the form of
damaged corps, flattened houses and power cuts.
</P>
<P>
At least 20 districts in eastern Nepal were affected by the
short but fierce storm. 
