<HEADLINE> Boeing, BAE Apply to Invest in South Korea's Aerospace Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Boeing and BAE Systems have jointly
applied to buy part of the stake of Korea Aerospace Industries (
KAI), said the KAI Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two aerospace firms formed a consortium for joint
investment last Friday when the KAI closed its international
bidding.
</P>
<P>
The KAI, a joint venture established by Daewoo Heavy Industries,
Samsung Aerospace and Hyundai Space and Aircraft last October,
possesses total assets of 1.05 trillion won (almost 1 billion U.S.
dollars) and expects to attract around 200 billion won (about 182
million dollars) of foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Global Alliance, which consists of Lockheed Martin,
Aerospatiale and Dassault, has also reportedly participated in the
competition to take up the KAI's stake, but there was no
confirmation from the KAI. 
