<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Ban TV Smoking Ads, Publicities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is likely to be the
first Asian country to ban all publicities and advertisements of
cigarettes and smoking on television, according to the official
Thai News Agency Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Prakit Vetisathokkij, Secretary-General of the Bangkok-based
Foundation for Non-Smoking Campaigns, was quoted as saying that
the Thai government is pushing for an amended bill through the
parliament to prohibit the practice of broadcasting smoking
advertisements and publicities on TV.
</P>
<P>
If the amended bill is promulgated, Thailand would be the first
country in Asia to ban TV publicities and advertisements of
tobacco products, he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the government to speedily push for the enactment of
the amended bill, saying some developed countries in Europe and
North America have already had similar laws in place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
