<HEADLINE> Two Black Swans Killed by Dog in French Zoo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Two black swans were killed on
Sunday by at least one dog in a zoo in Nancy, eastern France, the
Agence France-Presse reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Last week, two Siberian bears were poisoned to death by unknown
people in the same zoo.
</P>
<P>
A staff member of the zoo said that one of the swans died on
the spot and the other died of serious injuries later.
</P>
<P>
The zoo had three female black swans and was considering to
exchange one of them with a male swan to make a couple before the
incident took place. 
</P>
