<HEADLINE> Nigerian Regular Container Cargo Ship Detained in E. China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Ningbo Maritime Court in East
China's Zhejiang Province on Sunday detained a regular container
cargo ship from Nigeria and ordered the Nigerian shipping company
pay 300,000 U.S. dollars as guarantee money on charges that the
ship was responsible for severe damaging a Chinese fishing boat in
early April.
</P>
<P>
The Nigeria ship, W/Vabuja, was said to have crashed into a
Chinese fishing boat on April 2 in the East China Sea near Ningbo,
causing heavy damage to the Chinese boat, and seriously injuring
five fishermen, who are still being treated in hospital, according
to sources with the Ningbo Maritime Court.
</P>
<P>
Estimated damages were set at more than 250,000 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The six fishermen filed a lawsuit with the Ningbo Maritime
Court on Sunday, and the court handed down its decision on the
same day.
</P>
<P>
The case remains under further review. 
</P>
