<HEADLINE> Forum on Nuclear Power Development Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of
Engineering (CAE) held a forum on the development strategy of
nuclear power in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Coal accounts for the majority of energy consumption in China,
which poses a big threat to the country's environment and
sustainable growth, said Pan Jiazheng, vice-president of the CAE.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out at the forum that to improve the energy
structure, develop waterpower, nuclear power and new kinds of
energy, and reduce environment pollution are the major issues
facing energy research and development.
</P>
<P>
A group of academicians of the CAE and experts in nuclear power
have been invited to give speeches at the forum to help Chinese
scientific and technological workers learn more about the newest
developments in nuclear energy.
</P>
<P>
In January, the CAE held a forum on biological chips, which
received an enthusiastic response from participants. The CAE plans
to hold more such forums to promote academic exchanges, spread the
latest information in engineering development and improve the
quality of young engineers.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 experts and scholars attended today's forum.
</P>
</TEXT>
