<HEADLINE> Saudi, Iranian Defense Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Second Deputy Prime Minister,
Minister of Defense and Aviation, Inspector General Sultan ibn Abd
el-Aziz met with Iranian Minister of Defense and Armed Forces
Logistics Ali Shamkhani in the Red Sea resort of Jeddah on Monday
evening.
</P>
<P>
In the beginning of the meeting, Prince Sultan stressed that the
visit by Shamkhani is a reflection of the bilateral friendship and
will be conducive to co-operation between Iran and the Gulf Co-
operation Council (GCC), reported the Saudi News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Shamkhani said de-escalation and peaceful co-existence are
Iran's main approaches not only toward Saudi Arabia but toward all
brotherly countries of the GCC.
</P>
<P>
