told reporters that the high level visit exchanges between both
countries are the clearest evidence on the two-side pursuance of
proximity and better ties.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that they did not touch upon the Iraqi issue
because they were interested only in furthering the bilateral ties
and the Iranian-GCC relations.
</P>
<P>
On the Iran-U.A.E territorial dispute, Shamkhani said the issue
can be resolved through the continued talks between Tehran and Abu
Dhabi and the exchanged visits between the Iranian and U.A.E
officials.
</P>
<P>
Iran has been controlling the Gulf-based Islands of Minor and
Major Thomb and Abu Musa which are claimed by U.A.E as national
territories. 
</P>
