<HEADLINE> ADB Meeting to Boost tourism in Northern Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Upcoming 33rd meeting of the
board of governors of the Asian Development Bank (ADB) in northern
Thai province of Chiang Mai early next month is expected to help
boost tourism and related businesses in this renowned resort
province, local TV station reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The positive prospect of the tourism and related businesses in
Chiang Mai during the May 6-8 ADB meeting was anticipated after a
recent survey found that many meeting attendants had already
booked tour programs there, according to the TV news report.
</P>
<P>
The tour programs are mainly in the capital city of Chiang Mai
province and adjacent areas, including recreational places, as
well as local trade and cultural centers, it said.
</P>
<P>
The variety of local hand-made products is also believed to
attract the ADB delegates and other foreign arrivals in Chiang Mai
during the period, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Local hotel businesses would also be boosted, particularly
Westin Riverside Plaza Hotel, in which delegates attending the
meeting of the Manila-based bank would stay, it said. 
