<HEADLINE> Uganda Records 2.2 Million Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has recorded 2.2 million
people with disabilities (PWDs), and 55.6 percent of them have not
received any formal education, the Monitor daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
By January 2000, there were 150,559 children with disabilities
in school, and 42,325 mentally retarded children are not in school
and lack accommodation, said Macline Twimukye, executive director
of the National Union of Disabled Persons of Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Twimukye hailed the government for creating the Uganda National
 Institute of Special Education in 1996, and asked the government
to build at least one secondary school for PWDs. 
</P>
