<HEADLINE> China Opens Website on Western Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China has opened a website
containing a store of information on the country's nation-wide
campaign to develop the western areas.
</P>
<P>
The website can be accessed at two addresses: www.chinawest.com.
cn and www.westchina.com.cn.
</P>
<P>
According to Liu Zongchang, one of the operators, the website
was jointly built by northwest China's Shaanxi Province and other
western provinces and cities.
</P>
<P>
So far, the site offers an introduction to western China
provinces and municipalities and provides facts and figures on
government policies concerning the west development campaign,
major events, experts' forum, technical transfer, investment
projects, talents exchange programs and e-commerce.
</P>
<P>
China's strategy to develop its vast western part is a key task
for the central government this year and in coming years.
</P>
<P>
The drive is aimed to narrow the gap between China's vast
western areas and its prosperous coastal provinces. 
</P>
