<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Central Bank Teaches Public to Spot Fake Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China, the
central bank, will launch a publicity campaign in May to teach
people how to spot counterfeit Renminbi (RMB), the Chinese
currency.
</P>
<P>
China's State Council adopted the Regulations on the Management
of RMB in February, which stipulate that financial institutions
are obliged to educate the public about counterfeit money, and
they also must take measures to ensure that no phony or damaged
RMB gets into the hands of the public.
</P>
<P>
The regulations will go into effect on May 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
