<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Installed Power Capacity Exceeds 300 Million KW </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China has made a major
breakthrough in expanding its total installed power generating
capacity to 300 million kilowatts, according to Gao Yan, president
of the China State Power Corporation (CSPC).
</P>
<P>
Gao Yan said that CSPC has made great headway in restructuring
its power generation industry and in technological renovation,
which boosted its plan to transform CSPC into a giant corporation
with modern operating methods and a share-holding system.
</P>
<P>
Along with the sharp rise in the country's total installed
power generating capacity, China has given bigger play or put into
operation the large-sized generating units with capacity ranging
between 300,000 kw and 800,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the condenser tube generating units with generating
capacity less than 50,000 kw will be shut down gradually, Gao said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that CSPC expects to sell 845 billion kwh of
electricity and make a profit of 8.6 billion yuan by the end of
this year by restructuring the power industry and developing the
country's major power grids.
</P>
<P>
Also, China's power industry will undergo nationwide
technological renovations this year, which are designed to control
pollution, increase economic returns and guarantee safe operations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
