<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Insurance Regulatory Office Unveiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The China Insurance Regulatory
Commission (CIRC) announced here today that its Shanghai office,
the first of its local bodies, was officially launched today.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC said in a press release that the Guangzhou and Beijing
regulatory offices will be launched soon.
</P>
<P>
CIRC chairman Ma Yongwei said at the opening ceremony of its
Shanghai office that the establishment of the three local offices
is an important part of the reform of China's insurance regulatory
system and will actualize the CIRC's regulatory function in China'
s most important three local insurance markets.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the three cities reported a total premium income of 34.
8 billion yuan, accounting for 25 percent of the nation's total.
</P>
<P>
An overwhelming majority of foreign insurance companies and
their representative offices are also located in the three cities,
though the CIRC has recently opened Tianjin, Dalian, Chongqing and
other cities to foreign insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
The CIRC is also considering to set up regulatory offices in a
few other cities, which are expected to be operational by the end
of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
