<HEADLINE> China Urges U.S. for PNTR Approval </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua)-- The U.S. side should take concrete
measures to approve Permanent Normal Trade Relations for China in
time and without any conditions, otherwise it will greatly harm
the interests of American companies in China, said Foreign
Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi here today.
</P>
<P>
Sun reiterated at a regular press conference that the agreement
between China and the United States on China's WTO accession is a
win-win deal.
</P>
<P>
"It's no U.S. charity to China," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also said that China is seriously committed to
carrying out the agricultural cooperation agreement between China
and the U.S., and that the careful implementation of the agreement
is already under way.
</P>
<P>
However, he emphasized that a comprehensive implementation of
the agreement requests efforts from both sides. 
</P>
