<DOCNO> XIE20000425.0240 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Improves Product Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China's product quality has been
further improved during the first three months of this year, with
the qualification rate reaching 80.2 percent, the latest survey
shows.
</P>
<P>
This is the highest product qualification rate over the past
four years, according to the State Bureau of Quality and Technical
Supervision.
</P>
<P>
The quality of 31 varieties of products, including
refrigerators, detergent, pressure cookers and household gas ovens,
has been greatly improved. And the quality of cosmetics and other
ten categories of products remains good, compared with former spot
checks.
</P>
<P>
However, low quality rate was reported for 18 types of goods,
among them vegetable seeds, wood furniture and porcelain dishware.
</P>
<P>
An official from the bureau said that inferior products are
mostly produced by small-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The sample examination also indicated that China should
readjust the product mix in some sectors, such as color picture
tubes for TV sets, batteries and steel wire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
