<DOCNO> XIE20000425.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most China-Made Cosmetics of Good Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The latest random sampling of
China-made cosmetics shows that most get points for good quality
and none contained excessive heavy metal elements.
</P>
<P>
The spot check, conducted by the State Bureau of Quality and
Technical Supervision among 83 varieties of cosmetics produced and
sold in six provinces and municipalities, determined that 98.8
percent of the products were up to state standard.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, 66 types of cosmetics were tested for their
content of heavy metal elements, and 100 percent were up to the
state standards, the bureau said today.
</P>
<P>
Heavy metal elements including lead, arsenic and mercury in
cosmetics are health hazards.
</P>
<P>
However, experts pointed out that most of the raw materials and
compounds used to make China's cosmetics are imported from foreign
countries. They suggested Chinese cosmetic producers should
develop their own unique products that combine traditional Chinese
herbal medicine with modern technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
