<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Closure of One Iranian Reformist Daily Revoked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Head of Tehran Justice Department
Abasali Alizadeh said late Monday night that the closure of the
reformist daily Sobh-e Emrouz (This Morning) was revoked by the
judiciary.
</P>
<P>
Alizadeh said that the reason for the decision was absence of
the daily's managing director at a time of the meeting of the press
supervisory board, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Saeed Hajjarian, managing director of Sobh-e Emrouz and a
reformist ally of President Mohammad Khatami, was shot and
seriously wounded in an assassination attempt on March 12. He has
recovered his consciousness after a long coma, but is still
hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
The conservative judiciary on Monday ordered the closure of two
more reformist dailies Sobh-e Emrouz and Akhbar-e Eqtessad
(Economic News) and it closed down 12 reformist publications Sunday
night.
</P>
<P>
The unusual closure of so many reformist publications came amid
the intensifying struggle between the conservative and reformist
camps since the reformists' landslide victory in the elections.
</P>
<P>
A dozen of reformist journalists and publishers have been
summoned to courts and three journalists and publishers have been
sent to prisons on charge of insulting the Islamic sanctities and
principles.
</P>
<P>
The closure of papers has triggered condemnation from many
reformist circles, including the Association of Journalists and the
Islamic Human Rights Commission, who termed the judiciary's act as
violating the press freedom spirit stipulated in the constitution.
</P>
<P>
However, the reformist camp which support the reform programs of
President Khatami called for calm and legal actions against the
conservative crackdown.
</P>
<P>
President Khatami on Monday also called for calm and solidarity
in the society, particularly before the transition of the
parliament to the reformists from the powerful conservatives, who
still control most of the sensitive state organs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
