<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Kazakh Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
said today that the further development of good-neighborly, mutual-
benefit relations geared toward the 21st century between China and
Kazakhstan and their armed forces will help to build up the two
countries and their armies, and will help to ensure peace and
development in the region and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission, made
the remarks in a meeting with Kazakh Defense Minister S.
Tokpakbayev here today.
</P>
<P>
