Tajikistan held the first meeting in Astana, capital of Kazakhstan,
last month, Hu said, adding that China was satisfied with the
results of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries have reached consensus on many
major regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Tokpakbayev said that relations between the two countries and
armed forces have been developing smoothly in recent years, and
the 1,700-plus-kilometer border between the two countries has
become a bond of peace and friendship.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Kazakh government firmly supports China's
position on the issues of Taiwan, the human rights and opposition
to national separatism, and is also grateful for China's support
in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan is willing to work with China to safeguard peace and
stability in the Asia-Pacific region and the world, he added.
</P>
