<HEADLINE> Macao Airport to Handle Small Commercial Aircraft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The principal part of the aerial transport center was completed
at the end of year, and the installing and testing of related
facilities are well underway, according to sources with the
airport.
</P>
<P>
In the coming days, the local civil aviation authority and fire-
fighting department will check on the transport center. If all
things go smoothly, the center may be put into use by the end of
the month.
</P>
<P>
Covering more than 2,100 sq m, the transport center includes a
hangar which accommodate two small airplanes, and a parking apron
which is able to handle six planes.
</P>
<P>
