<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Road Project to East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
said Tuesday that it has approved a 29.8 million-U.S.-dollar
project in East Timor to undertake emergency road repairs, expand
Dili port facilities and restore electricity.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said in a press release that the Emergency
Infrastructure Rehabilitation Project will facilitate the delivery
of food and agricultural supplies, the resettlement of displaced
persons and the movement of the U.N. Peacekeeping Forces.
</P>
<P>
The project will also support financial management of East
Timor's power sector and capacity building of transport sector
institutions.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, the project is being financed by a
grant from the Trust Fund for East Timor which was established
with contributions from many donors.
</P>
<P>
East Timor's roads and electricity supply were severely damaged
in the recent conflict and their poor state hampers relief efforts
and security operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
