of the Netherlands in the JAPFA Classic International Chess
Tournament in Bali, Indonesia, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here Tuesday, Polgar, who is the
only women's player in the tournament, used the Queen Indian
defense to beat Timman in the 33rd move.
</P>
<P>
It was the second win in a row, and put her further into
contention as one of the hot favorites at the 56,500 U.S. dollars
tournament.
</P>
<P>
In another table, Anatoly Karpov of Russia tied with Gilberto
Milos of Brazil in the 49th move by using the Catalan opening and
Zaw Win Lay of Myanmar lost to American Yasser Seirawan in the
56th move with the Caro Kann defense.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's grand master Utut Adianto bounced back from his
second day defeat when he beat Estonian Jaan Ehlvest in the 30th
move, but fellow countryman Ruben Gunawan failed to overcome the
1999 FIDE world champion Alexander Khalifman.
</P>
