Nazarbayev was elected the first president of Kazakhstan for a
six-year term in April 1990, and his tenure was extended to the
year 2000 in a referendum in April 1995.
</P>
<P>
He was reelected in the presidential elections in January 1999,
after the parliament approved an amendment to the constitution in
October 1998, which decided to hold the elections ahead of
schedule and extend the presidency to seven years. 
