<HEADLINE> Germany to Clash Hungary in Women's Table Tennis Team Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Germany is one step close to their
third consecutive team title after they routed Croatia 4-0 on
Monday to reach the European table tennis women's team final.
</P>
<P>
Germany will play Hungary, who slashed Russia by the same
margin, for the title on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hungary and Germany have collected 11 women's European team
crowns between them since the first championships in 1958.
</P>
<P>
Germany will bid for a fifth gold and become the first country
to complete a hat-trick in the women's competition if they win the
final.
</P>
<P>
In the men's team event on Monday, Poland and Denmark won their
fifth round ties to finish second in their groups and book the two
remaining places for the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Germany and Sweden, newly-crowned world champions in Malaysia
in February, had secured a berth in the last four in Sunday's
penultimate round.
</P>
<P>
Poland beat Belgium 4-1 and will meet Sweden while Denmark face
Germany. 
</P>
