<HEADLINE> Man United Wins Again to Hit Chelsea's Euro Hopes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- League champions Manchester United
celebrated the title in style on Monday with 3-2 win over Chelsea
in front of more than 61,000 happy Old Trafford fans.
</P>
<P>
At the other end of the table Bradford City were clinging on
after a 1-0 win at Sunderland while Derby County looked safe after
beating Southampton 2-0.
</P>
<P>
While Manchester United, who secured the title on Saturday,
were able to enjoy a holiday stroll, the defeat severely hits
Chelsea's hopes of European soccer next season.
</P>
<P>
