<HEADLINE> Kenyan Coast Hotel Destroyed by Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A new hotel, the Garoda Coral
Beach Hotel, on Kenya's North Coast was destroyed by fire over the
weekend, media here reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The blaze, fanned by strong winds, raged through 25 private
villas plus 13 hotel rooms and other cottages, burning down
property valued at more than 5.7 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Garoda Coral Beach Hotel, a sister hotel of the Blue Bay
Village, Watamu, was ready to open at any time.
</P>
<P>
The fire started when burning garbage was blown onto the roofs
of the buildings, the police said, adding that they fought the
fire for more than five hours before giving up the struggle.
</P>
<P>
The police warned local residents to be careful when burning
garbage to avoid accidental spread of fires, especially during the
dry season.
</P>
<P>
The full extent of the losses could not be established
immediately because the manager of the hotel and the villa owners
are still abroad, the police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
