peaceful co-existence of the war veterans and the white farmers
while a peaceful solution is being worked out.
</P>
<P>
She told a press conference to mark the opening of this year's
tobacco marketing season that such a co-existence would allow
cropping programs to continue.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, the war veterans and the white
farmers agreed during a recent meeting with President Robert
Mugabe to make consultations in finding a solution to the land
crisis which had caused the former freedom fighter invading
white-owned farms willy-nilly.
</P>
<P>
Mujuru commended tobacco farmers for producing good quality
crop and hoped that this would encourage merchants to pay fair
prices that would encourage farmers to continue growing the crop.
</P>
<P>
"Farmers should continue to do their pre-planting for tobacco
and wheat winter crops while consultations between farmers and war
veterans continue," she said.
</P>
<P>
Tobacco auction will start on Wednesday and about 220 million
kilograms of flue cured are expected to be sold this season
against last season's 196 million kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Tobacco is Zimbabwe's biggest foreign currency earner. It
earned about 500 million U.S. dollars for the country during the
last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
