<HEADLINE> U.S. Senate Plans Hearings on Elian's Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 25 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Senate Republicans
criticized Attorney General Janet Reno Tuesday for the forceful
seizure of Cuban boy Elian Gonzalez from his Miami relatives and
said they would hold hearings on the raid Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A Senate delegation led by Majority leader Trent Lott held a
two-hour closed-door meeting with Reno on Capital Hill.
</P>
<P>
"I felt like a number of questions were not adequately
answered, particularly why did they use this force on that
particular day," Lott told reporters after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
"Perhaps we may get a clearer answer to some of these questions
in a public hearing," he said.
</P>
<P>
Lott said the Senate Judiciary Committee would hold hearings
soon and may call government officials, lawyers and members of the
Gonzalez family to testify.
</P>
<P>
Florida Republican Senator Connie Mack also said that he was "
horrified that our government would use armed force in a family
home to remove a 6-year-old child at gunpoint."
</P>
<P>
Elian has stayed together with his father Juan Miguel at
Andrews Air Force base outside Washington since Saturday and they
will shift to an estate at Wye River east of Washington.  
</P>
