<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Edo Ronchi, the Italian minister for
the environment in the outgoing government, turned down Italian
Premier-designate Giuliano Amato's offer to take over European
Union policy Minister in the new cabinet in a letter to the
premier-designate made public late Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
In his letter, Ronchi said he thought it was a "serious mistake
" to remove the environment portfolio from the Greens but went on
to"confirm, however, my parliamentary support and best wishes for
the success of your government."
</P>
<P>
Amato nominated 24 ministers in presidential palace Tuesday
evening, and he moved Ronchi to ministry of European Union policy,
and nominated Willer Bordon to hold the job of environment in the
cabinet
</P>
<P>
Amato point out that he succeeded in trimming portfolios from
25 to 24 by combining the industry with foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The premier-designate also noted that this government has two
technicians, and they can be easily recognized by their names. One
is Professor Tullio De Mauro, tapped for education, and the other
is Doctor Umberto Veronesi, a leading oncologist given the public
health portfolio.
</P>
<P>
Amato's confidence test is expected to come Thursday in the
Lower House and calculations indicate that he will be able to
count on fewer than 320 votes against 297 for the opposition
Freedom Front, with another nine deputies wavering and talking
abstention. 
