<HEADLINE> Mercosur Drugs Meeting Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Southern Common Market's (
Mercosur) first drug meeting was opened Tuesday in Argentina's
capital.
</P>
<P>
General Secretary of Argentine Presidency Jorge De la Rua
attended the inauguration describing the event shows "the
philosophy of consolidating Mercosur not as a mere economic-
regional accord, but rather as a historical, cultural and
educational integration".
</P>
<P>
The appointment also serves to show the government's firm
conviction in the frontal and decisive battle against the drug
problem, stressed the official, who attended the encounter,
representing President Fernando De la Rua.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which will go on till Wednesday, counts with the
participation of representatives from Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay,
Paraguay, Chile and Bolivia, organized by Secretariat of Drug
Addiction Prevention and Fight against Drug Traffic from Argentina.
</P>
<P>
This event is to discuss and find an instrument allowing
countries to generate common policies and programs, cooperation
activities, training and exchange of information for the fighting
of drugs and the prevention of drug using. 
