<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose sharply
Tuesday as investors rushed in the technology sector for bargain-
hunting amid strong corporate earnings reports.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index closed up 228.75 at
3,711.23, bouncing back from steep falling. The index fell 311.09
points in total in the previous three sessions.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 218.72 at 11,124.82,
extending its gain of 231.14 points in the previous two sessions.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 47.58 at 1,477.44.
</P>
<P>
The market rallied as strong earnings reports encouraged
investors to move back to the technology stocks. Corning, which
has transformed its business in recent years to focus on fiber
optics, reported that its first quarter operating earnings reached
64 cents a share, well above 55 cents per share in expectations.
</P>
<P>
Among other technology companies reporting strong earnings in
the first quarter were Priceline.com, the name-your-price Internet
company, and Sapient, a technology consulting company. Microsoft
also recovered from a big selloff Monday.
</P>
<P>
Technology and financial companies led the Dow's advance. Intel
and American Express rose.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 16.59 at 658.77 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 15.32 at 896.04. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 20.49 at 489.03.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 13-to-5 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 2,217 up, 844 down and 399
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 1.06 billion shares from 865.88
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
